The paper discusses the theoretical properties of adversarial training for neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on the computational properties of adversarial training, which suggests that it may also fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of gradient descent in the training process suggests that it may also be relevant to the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the robustness of adversarial training, which is a topic that falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
